Prompt to Create Website
Write a complete code for responsive website using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

Context:
    I want a website for [উদ্দেশ্য লিখুন].

Structure:

    Possible Structure Elements for a Website
    1. Navigation / Header
        o Navbar (with links, dropdowns)
        o Logo / Branding
        o Hamburger menu (mobile)
        o Search bar
    2. Hero Section / Banner
        o Big headline / tagline
        o Background image or video
        o Call-to-Action buttons (CTA)
        o Animated elements / sliders
    3. About Section
        o Text content describing company / platform / person
        o Images or illustrations
    4. Services / Features / Cards
        o Feature cards (with icon, title, description)
        o Service list or offerings
        o Hover effects / interactive components
    5. Portfolio / Gallery / Projects
        o Image or video gallery
        o Filters / categories
        o Carousel / slider
    6. Testimonials / Reviews
        o Customer feedback
        o Rating stars
        o Carousel / slider
    7. Pricing / Plans Section
        o Pricing tables
        o Subscription plans
        o Call-to-action buttons
    8. FAQ Section
        o Accordion style expandable questions
        o Searchable FAQs
    9. Blog / News Section
        o List of articles with images, titles, date
        o Pagination
    10. Contact Section / Form
        o Contact form (name, email, message)
        o Map integration
        o Social links
    11. Call-to-Action Section (CTA)
        o Highlighted section to drive user action
        o Buttons / links
    12. Footer
        o Contact info / address
        o Social media icons
        o Newsletter subscription
        o Quick links / Sitemap
    13. Other Optional Components
        o Modal / Popup windows
        o Back-to-top button
        o Loading animation / Preloader
        o Floating action button (FAB)
        o Chatbot widget

Design:

    Possible Design Styles / Features for a Website
    1. Background Styles
        • Gradient background (linear, radial, angular)
        • Solid color background
        • Image background (full screen, section-wise)
        • Video background
        • Pattern / Texture background
        • Parallax scrolling background
    2. Glassmorphism / Frosted Glass Effects
        • Semi-transparent containers with blur
        • Transparent cards with shadows
        • Frosted navbar / header
    3. Color Themes / Modes
        • Light mode
        • Dark mode
        • Auto switch (light/dark based on system preference)
        • Custom color palette (brand colors)
    4. Typography / Text Design
        • Custom fonts (Google Fonts, system fonts)
        • Font sizes for headings, body, buttons
        • Text shadows
        • Letter spacing / line height adjustments
        • Gradient text
        • Animated typing effect / text animations
    5. Buttons / Interactive Elements
        • Hover effects (lift, shadow, color change, gradient shift)
        • Rounded corners (pill, circle, small radius)
        • Shadow / elevation
        • Animated icons on hover
        • Ripple effect
    6. Cards / Containers
        • Shadow / elevation (material design)
        • Rounded corners
        • Hover lift effect
        • Glassmorphic cards (blur + transparency)
        • Gradient or image overlay
    7. Icons / Graphics
        • Font Awesome icons
        • Material icons
        • SVG graphics / animations
        • Lottie animations
        • Animated illustrations
    8. Animations / Transitions
        • Fade-in / fade-out
        • Slide-in / slide-out
        • Hover animations
        • Scroll-triggered animations
        • Page load animations
    9. Layout / Responsiveness
        • Flexbox layout
        • CSS Grid layout
        • Mobile-first responsive design
        • Breakpoints for desktop, tablet, mobile
        • Adaptive font sizes and padding
    10. Navigation / Header Styles
        • Sticky / fixed header
        • Transparent navbar
        • Hamburger menu for mobile
        • Animated underline for links
        • Dropdown / mega menu
    11. Forms / Input Design
        • Rounded input fields
        • Floating labels
        • Shadow / glow on focus
        • Animated submit button
    12. Footer / Miscellaneous
        • Shadowed footer
        • Gradient / colored footer
        • Interactive social icons
        • Back-to-top button
    13. Special Effects
        • Neumorphism / soft UI
        • Skeuomorphic buttons
        • Scroll-based parallax
        • Particle animation background
        • Video or GIF animation

Functionality:

    Possible Website Functionalities / Features
    1. Navigation / Menu
        • Hamburger menu toggle (open/close)
        • Dropdown / Mega menu
        • Sticky / fixed navbar
        • Scroll spy (active link highlight on scroll)
        • Smooth scroll to sections
        • Dynamic loading from external file (e.g., fetch API)
    2. Buttons / Links
        • Links to other pages
        • Call-to-action buttons (CTA)
        • Smooth hover / click animations
        • Disabled / enabled states
        • Scroll-to-top button
    3. Forms / User Input
        • Contact forms (name, email, message)
        • Search forms
        • Login / Signup forms
        • Form validation (required fields, email check, password check)
        • File upload / download forms
        • Inline error messages
    4. Interactive Components
        • Modals / popups
        • Tooltips
        • Accordions / expandable sections (FAQ style)
        • Tabs / Tabbed interface
        • Carousels / Sliders
        • Image / video lightbox
    5. Content Loading / API
        • Fetch / AJAX data loading
        • Dynamic content update without page reload
        • JSON / API integration
        • Infinite scroll / lazy loading
    6. Animations / Effects
        • Hover animations (buttons, cards, images)
        • Scroll-triggered animations
        • Fade / slide / zoom animations
        • Page load animations
        • Lottie or SVG animations
    7. Media Handling
        • Image galleries / sliders / carousels
        • Video embedding / background video
        • Audio playback
        • PDF viewer / download button
    8. User Experience Enhancements
        • Responsive typography
        • Mobile-friendly design
        • Dark/light mode toggle
        • Theme switching
        • Smooth scrolling
        • Back-to-top button
    9. E-Commerce / Transactions (Optional)
        • Add-to-cart button
        • Product filtering / sorting
        • Checkout form
        • Payment gateway integration
    10. Authentication / User Account (Optional)
        • Login / Signup functionality
        • Profile page
        • Password reset / change
        • OAuth login (Google, Facebook, GitHub)
    11. Notifications / Feedback
        • Toast / popup notifications
        • Error / success messages
        • Loading spinner / progress bar
    12. Other Useful Functionalities
        • Sticky elements / headers
        • Tabs / collapsible sections
        • Scroll animations / parallax effect
        • Real-time updates / WebSockets
        • Chatbot widget
        • Offline support / PWA (Progressive Web App)

Output:

    Possible Output Requirements / Options
    1. File Structure
        • Full code in one file (HTML + CSS + JS)
        • Separate files for HTML, CSS, JS
        • Use external libraries (like Font Awesome, Google Fonts) via CDN
        • Use local libraries / assets
    2. Code Quality
        • Clean and readable code
        • Proper indentation
        • Comments explaining sections (HTML, CSS, JS)
        • Semantic HTML tags (header, main, footer, section, article, nav, etc.)
        • Efficient CSS and JS (avoid unnecessary duplication)
    3. Responsiveness
        • Mobile-first responsive design
        • Adaptive typography for desktop, tablet, mobile
        • Flexbox or CSS Grid layout
        • Media queries for different screen sizes
    4. Performance / Optimization
        • Minimize external requests
        • Lazy load images / assets
        • Use optimized images / icons
        • Efficient JS (event delegation, minimal DOM manipulation)
    5. Accessibility
        • Alt text for images
        • Proper ARIA labels if needed
        • Keyboard navigable (tabindex, focus styles)
    6. Design Fidelity
        • Maintain hover effects, shadows, rounded corners
        • Ensure gradients, glassmorphism, and theme colors are preserved
        • Smooth animations / transitions
    7. Output Format Options
        • Full standalone HTML file (self-contained)
        • Optionally separate CSS/JS files if project is large
        • Include external links via CDN or local files
        • Ready-to-run in browser without additional setup
